OL,3,CGaza medic's fear after 33 relatives
OL,4,Cincluding babies killed in Israeli
OL,5,Cbombings
OL,7,FWe ask him to describe his volunteer
OL,8,Fshifts. "What's strange," he says, "Is
OL,9,Fthat most of the wounded martyrs we
OL,10,Freceive are women and yes, women and
OL,11,Fchildren."
OL,13,FHe pauses, "small bodies, innocent
OL,14,Ffaces. Things that leave a wound in
OL,15,Fthe heart that will never heal".
OL,17,FIt's only three years since he turned
OL,18,F18.
OL,20,FBut like every Gazan, Hamza knows his
OL,21,Flife also hangs in the balance.
